The paper deals with computational learning and optimization, which are core topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of genetic algorithms and uniform crossover also suggests a focus on evolutionary computation and optimization. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves statistical hypothesis testing, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of algorithms and data structures to solve the learning problem also suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on optimization and efficiency could also place it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
